Since all CDI Beans are light-weight proxies, there is no real disadvantage. The comment about a logger being a singleton is not completely accurate, depending on how you implemented it. The following will inject the correct logger instance based on the target:

```
	@Produces
	@Dependent
	public Logger createLogger(final InjectionPoint injectionPoint) {
		Class&lt;?&gt; declaringClass = injectionPoint.getMember().getDeclaringClass();
		return LoggerFactory.getLogger(declaringClass);
	}
```

The advantage really comes down to testing... you can now mock the injection and test just your actual business code. Static functions are generally very hard to mock and this provides a very clean way of not needing to deal with them.

