Building on @iboisver&#39;s comment, you can separate them and are encouraged to do so in the [gradle docs][1]. You basically have to:

 1. Create a new directory under `src` (i.e. `src/integrationTest`)
 2. Add the source set in the `build.gradle` file along with it&#39;s configurations:
```
sourceSets {
	integrationTest {
		compileClasspath += sourceSets.main.output + sourceSets.test.output
		runtimeClasspath += sourceSets.main.output + sourceSets.test.output
	}
}

configurations {
	integrationTestImplementation.extendsFrom testImplementation
	integrationTestRuntimeOnly.extendsFrom testRuntime
}
```
 3. Create an `integrationTests` task to run your integration tests, and attach it to the `check` task (also in `build.gradle`):
```
task integrationTest(type: Test) {
	description = &#39;Runs integration tests.&#39;
	group = &#39;verification&#39;

	testClassesDirs = sourceSets.integrationTest.output.classesDirs
	classpath = sourceSets.integrationTest.runtimeClasspath
	shouldRunAfter test
}

check.dependsOn integrationTest
```

